The paper discusses the use of scientometric mapping as a tool for strategic intelligence in the governance of emerging technologies. The paper focuses on the biomedical domain and uses publication and patent data to map the emergence of RNA interference, HPV testing technologies, and TPMT genetic testing. This suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
